        "content": "<p>Is there a proof that the function <code>compContinuousLinearMapCLM</code> is continuous?</p>\n<p>Observe that this function simply sends a continuous linear map  <code>f : M â†’L[ğ•œ] M'</code>to a continuous linear map <code>(M' [â‹€^Î¹]â†’L[ğ•œ] N) â†’L[ğ•œ] (M [â‹€^Î¹]â†’L[ğ•œ] N)</code> acting via precomposition in each slot. That is, for any <code>g : M' [â‹€^Î¹]â†’L[ğ•œ] N</code>, the function <code>compContinuousLinearMapCLM f g</code> is simply the function <code>vâ‚, ..., váµ¢ â†¦ g (f vâ‚, ..., f váµ¢)</code>. One intuitively feels operator should be continuous, at least in the case when <code>Î¹</code> is finite, but I'm not quite sure how to prove it yet. Note that when <code>M, M'</code> are finite dimensional this result is immediate because <code>f</code> is essentially just a matrix.</p>\n<p>Note that the analogous function for post-composition by a continuous linear map <code>ContinuousLinearMap.compContinuousAlternatingMapCLM</code> is continuous. And, in fact, it is implemented in Mathlib as a continuous linear map, so this fact is easily accessible by simply calling <code>(ContinuousLinearMap.compContinuousAlternatingMapCLM ğ•œ M M' N).cont</code></p>\n<p>Here is a MWE for what I am looking for.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Topology</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Basic</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Topology</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Alternating</span><